<paragraph blockId="1.[160,1156,662,1727]" box="[160,276,662,687]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">
<heading bold="true" box="[160,276,662,687]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550" reason="0">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,662,687]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[160,1156,662,1727]" lastBlockId="2.[160,1155,1518,1576]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="1551" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">
The female has unique characteristics among 
<taxonomicName box="[675,801,698,722]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pompilidae</taxonomicName>
in having a remarkably shaped head, its outline rhomboid in frontal view (
<figureCitation box="[714,812,732,756]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[160,225,1364,1387]" captionTargetBox="[183,1126,163,1298]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1153,142,1333]" captionText="Figure 1. Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov., holotype (A, B, E, F) and paratype (C, D, G – I) females: (A – C), (F) head (A, frontal view; B, lateral view; C, posterior view; F, dorsal view); (D) pro-, meso- and metanota, dorsolateral view; (E) left hind tarsal claw, outer view; (G) left maxilla, inner view; (H) maxillary palpus; (I) labium, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159019/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figure 1</figureCitation>
A) and triangular in profile (
<figureCitation box="[167,257,767,791]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[160,225,1364,1387]" captionTargetBox="[183,1126,163,1298]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1153,142,1333]" captionText="Figure 1. Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov., holotype (A, B, E, F) and paratype (C, D, G – I) females: (A – C), (F) head (A, frontal view; B, lateral view; C, posterior view; F, dorsal view); (D) pro-, meso- and metanota, dorsolateral view; (E) left hind tarsal claw, outer view; (G) left maxilla, inner view; (H) maxillary palpus; (I) labium, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159019/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figure 1</figureCitation>
B); upper frons strongly produced anteriorly, hence supra-antennal area overhanging radicle of scape; lower frons markedly receding posteriorly, greatly narrowed below, flattened. The following characteristics are also very specialised and, together with the above traits, distinguish this genus from others: (1) body very slender (
<figureCitation box="[168,263,906,930]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figure 2</figureCitation>
A); (2) mesosoma and metasoma compressed laterally; (3) upper frons with several long, stout, suberect setae (
<figureCitation box="[567,667,940,964]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[160,225,1364,1387]" captionTargetBox="[183,1126,163,1298]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1153,142,1333]" captionText="Figure 1. Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov., holotype (A, B, E, F) and paratype (C, D, G – I) females: (A – C), (F) head (A, frontal view; B, lateral view; C, posterior view; F, dorsal view); (D) pro-, meso- and metanota, dorsolateral view; (E) left hind tarsal claw, outer view; (G) left maxilla, inner view; (H) maxillary palpus; (I) labium, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159019/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figures 1</figureCitation>
A, B); (4) inner orbits strongly arcuate and remarkably convergent below; (5) eye with numerous erect setulae, those being much longer than facet width; (6) clypeus small, entirely flattened; (7) antenna not convolute (
<figureCitation box="[168,271,1044,1068]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figures 2</figureCitation>
A, 3); (8) juncture of anterior and posterior faces of vertex sharply edged; (9) posterior faces of vertex and gena concave, smooth and highly polished, without occipital carina (
<figureCitation box="[351,442,1114,1138]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[160,225,1364,1387]" captionTargetBox="[183,1126,163,1298]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1153,142,1333]" captionText="Figure 1. Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov., holotype (A, B, E, F) and paratype (C, D, G – I) females: (A – C), (F) head (A, frontal view; B, lateral view; C, posterior view; F, dorsal view); (D) pro-, meso- and metanota, dorsolateral view; (E) left hind tarsal claw, outer view; (G) left maxilla, inner view; (H) maxillary palpus; (I) labium, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159019/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figure 1</figureCitation>
C); (10) pronotum much longer than mesoscutum at midline (
<figureCitation box="[168,255,1148,1172]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[160,225,1364,1387]" captionTargetBox="[183,1126,163,1298]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1153,142,1333]" captionText="Figure 1. Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov., holotype (A, B, E, F) and paratype (C, D, G – I) females: (A – C), (F) head (A, frontal view; B, lateral view; C, posterior view; F, dorsal view); (D) pro-, meso- and metanota, dorsolateral view; (E) left hind tarsal claw, outer view; (G) left maxilla, inner view; (H) maxillary palpus; (I) labium, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159019/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figure 1</figureCitation>
D); (11) pronotal collar slightly depressed below level of its dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[1035,1126,1148,1172]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figure 2</figureCitation>
B); (12) oblique sulcus on mesepisternum subobsolete (
<figureCitation box="[798,897,1183,1207]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figure 2</figureCitation>
C); (13) mesepimeron entirely obsolete, save for its upper margin (
<figureCitation box="[697,792,1218,1242]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figure 2</figureCitation>
C, arrow); (14) metapostnotum completely invaginated dorsally; (15) lower metapleuron and lateral side of propodeum fairly flattened, smooth and highly polished (
<figureCitation box="[669,759,1287,1311]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figure 2</figureCitation>
C); (16) pterostigma very small and triangular, its base much shorter than cross vein 2r-rs (
<figureCitation box="[775,867,1322,1346]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figure 2</figureCitation>
D); (17) marginal cell very long and narrow, strongly tapering apically (
<figureCitation box="[664,755,1356,1380]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figure 2</figureCitation>
E); (18) vein M reaching outer wing margin; (19) hind wing with only one basal hamulus; (20) hind wing cross vein cu-a short and almost straight, originating very basally to fork of vein M+CuA, forming an obtuse angle with vein 1A (
<figureCitation box="[397,490,1460,1484]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figure 2</figureCitation>
F); (21) jugal lobe very small; (22) outer face of fore coxa flattened, with a fine, semi-circularly curved groove posteriorly from base to apex (
<figureCitation box="[167,262,1530,1554]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figure 2</figureCitation>
G, arrow); (23) fore femur enormously incrassate (
<figureCitation box="[849,943,1530,1554]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figure 2</figureCitation>
G); (24) hind coxa much larger than mid coxa, strongly compressed laterally, greatly raised and lamellate dorso-innerly, smooth and polished, forming the same plane with both lower metapleuron and lateral face of propodeum (
<figureCitation box="[609,699,1634,1658]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figure 2</figureCitation>
B); (25) outer apicoventral corner of hind femur rounded; (26) orbicula minute, with its pecten consisting of a few radiating, almost straight weak setulae; (27) all tarsal claws edentate (
<figureCitation box="[866,958,1703,1727]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[160,225,1364,1387]" captionTargetBox="[183,1126,163,1298]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1153,142,1333]" captionText="Figure 1. Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov., holotype (A, B, E, F) and paratype (C, D, G – I) females: (A – C), (F) head (A, frontal view; B, lateral view; C, posterior view; F, dorsal view); (D) pro-, meso- and metanota, dorsolateral view; (E) left hind tarsal claw, outer view; (G) left maxilla, inner view; (H) maxillary palpus; (I) labium, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159019/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="1550">Figure 1</figureCitation>
E); (28) tergum I narrowed and parallel sided basally (
<figureCitation box="[602,698,1518,1542]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551">Figure 2</figureCitation>
A); and (29) sternum VI strongly compressed laterally, with a median carina (
<figureCitation box="[615,707,1552,1576]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551">Figure 2</figureCitation>
<collectionCode box="[707,726,1552,1576]" country="Finland" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15618" name="University of Helsinki" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551">H</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159019/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551" targetBox="[183,1126,163,1298]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[160,1156,1364,1475]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,252,1364,1387]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551">Figure 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[260,458,1364,1387]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Aberropompilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dayi" status="sp. nov.">
