, holotype (A, B, E, F) and paratype (C, D, G–I) females: (A–C), (F) head (A, frontal view; B, lateral view; C, posterior view; F, dorsal view); (D) pro-, meso- and metanota, dorsolateral view; (E) left hind tarsal claw, outer view; (G) left maxilla, inner view; (H) maxillary palpus; (I) labium, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="1553" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551" type="multiple">
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="1553" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[160,1155,1633,1727]" box="[160,294,1633,1658]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551">
<heading bold="true" box="[160,294,1633,1658]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551" reason="0">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,294,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[160,1155,1633,1727]" lastBlockId="3.[160,1156,1041,1724]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="1552" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551">
Body smooth and impunctate. Ocelli forming low obtuse-angled triangle (
<figureCitation box="[1033,1124,1669,1693]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[160,225,1364,1387]" captionTargetBox="[183,1126,163,1298]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1153,142,1333]" captionText="Figure 1. Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov., holotype (A, B, E, F) and paratype (C, D, G – I) females: (A – C), (F) head (A, frontal view; B, lateral view; C, posterior view; F, dorsal view); (D) pro-, meso- and metanota, dorsolateral view; (E) left hind tarsal claw, outer view; (G) left maxilla, inner view; (H) maxillary palpus; (I) labium, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159019/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551">Figure 1</figureCitation>
<collectionCode box="[1125,1142,1669,1693]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15707" name="Field Museum of Natural History, Botany Department" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551">F</collectionCode>
). Malar space much longer than one-half width of mandibular base (
<figureCitation box="[938,1027,1703,1727]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[160,225,1364,1387]" captionTargetBox="[183,1126,163,1298]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1153,142,1333]" captionText="Figure 1. Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov., holotype (A, B, E, F) and paratype (C, D, G – I) females: (A – C), (F) head (A, frontal view; B, lateral view; C, posterior view; F, dorsal view); (D) pro-, meso- and metanota, dorsolateral view; (E) left hind tarsal claw, outer view; (G) left maxilla, inner view; (H) maxillary palpus; (I) labium, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159019/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551">Figure 1</figureCitation>
<collectionCodeEnum box="[1027,1046,1703,1727]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551">
<collectionCode box="[1027,1046,1703,1727]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15534" name="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Zentraleinrichtung der Freien Universitaet" pageId="2" pageNumber="1551">B</collectionCode>
</collectionCodeEnum>
). Labrum small, fairly exposed beneath clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[604,694,1041,1065]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[160,225,1364,1387]" captionTargetBox="[183,1126,163,1298]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1153,142,1333]" captionText="Figure 1. Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov., holotype (A, B, E, F) and paratype (C, D, G – I) females: (A – C), (F) head (A, frontal view; B, lateral view; C, posterior view; F, dorsal view); (D) pro-, meso- and metanota, dorsolateral view; (E) left hind tarsal claw, outer view; (G) left maxilla, inner view; (H) maxillary palpus; (I) labium, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159019/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Figure 1</figureCitation>
<collectionCodeEnum box="[693,714,1041,1065]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">
<collectionCode box="[693,714,1041,1065]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">A</collectionCode>
</collectionCodeEnum>
); apical margin feebly convex without median emargination. Mandible small, thin antero-posteriorly with small tooth subapically on inner margin, without lamina or fimbriate groove along outer margin. Maxilla with palpus elongate (
<figureCitation box="[422,523,1145,1169]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[160,225,1364,1387]" captionTargetBox="[183,1126,163,1298]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1153,142,1333]" captionText="Figure 1. Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov., holotype (A, B, E, F) and paratype (C, D, G – I) females: (A – C), (F) head (A, frontal view; B, lateral view; C, posterior view; F, dorsal view); (D) pro-, meso- and metanota, dorsolateral view; (E) left hind tarsal claw, outer view; (G) left maxilla, inner view; (H) maxillary palpus; (I) labium, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159019/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Figures 1</figureCitation>
G, H); last three palpomeres thinner than third, fourth longer than third. Labium with prementum without median cleft apically or circular or heart- or spade-shaped membranous area subapically (
<figureCitation box="[830,927,1215,1239]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[160,225,1364,1387]" captionTargetBox="[183,1126,163,1298]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1153,142,1333]" captionText="Figure 1. Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov., holotype (A, B, E, F) and paratype (C, D, G – I) females: (A – C), (F) head (A, frontal view; B, lateral view; C, posterior view; F, dorsal view); (D) pro-, meso- and metanota, dorsolateral view; (E) left hind tarsal claw, outer view; (G) left maxilla, inner view; (H) maxillary palpus; (I) labium, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159019/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">
Figure 
<date box="[917,937,1215,1239]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">1I</date>
</figureCitation>
). Antennal socket removed from upper margin of clypeus by much more than its long axis. Scape long, flattened and curved outward on outer face (
<figureCitation box="[680,768,1284,1308]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[160,225,1364,1387]" captionTargetBox="[183,1126,163,1298]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[163,1153,142,1333]" captionText="Figure 1. Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov., holotype (A, B, E, F) and paratype (C, D, G – I) females: (A – C), (F) head (A, frontal view; B, lateral view; C, posterior view; F, dorsal view); (D) pro-, meso- and metanota, dorsolateral view; (E) left hind tarsal claw, outer view; (G) left maxilla, inner view; (H) maxillary palpus; (I) labium, posterior view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159019/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Figure 1</figureCitation>
F).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552" targetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[160,1156,887,999]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,254,888,911]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Figure 2.</emphasis>
Holotype female of 
<taxonomicName box="[468,669,887,910]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Aberropompilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dayi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[468,669,887,910]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Aberropompilus dayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[679,761,888,911]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A–C, E–H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[160,1156,1041,1724]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">
Pronotum with anterior declivity much shorter than dorsum, gradually and uniformly merging into dorsum, thus never differentiated from dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[836,923,1353,1377]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Figure 2</figureCitation>
<collectionCode box="[923,939,1353,1377]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15534" name="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Zentraleinrichtung der Freien Universitaet" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">B</collectionCode>
); lateral face almost vertical and concave (
<figureCitation box="[410,502,1388,1412]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Figure 2</figureCitation>
A), juncture of lateral and dorsal faces narrowly rounded. Dorsal surface of pronotum, mesoscutum and scutellar disc flattened, almost conforming to the same plane (
<figureCitation box="[340,427,1457,1481]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Figure 2</figureCitation>
B). Posterolateral margin of mesoscutum not raised. Axilla (cuneoli) practically absent. Propodeal dorsum much longer than declivity, flattened, and gradually merging into latter (
<figureCitation box="[383,471,1527,1551]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Figure 2</figureCitation>
C); declivity somewhat concave posteromedially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[160,1156,1041,1724]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">
Third abscissa of fore wing vein M (basal vein) curved anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[963,1056,1561,1585]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Figure 2</figureCitation>
E). Cross veins 2 and 3 rs-m almost straightly slanting and subparallel. Cross vein 2 m-cu meeting vein CuA1 much less than half of distance from base of CuA1 to wing margin. Vein CuA1 slightly deflected downward basally. Cross vein cu-a originating basally to fork of vein M+CuA.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[160,1060,1125,1148]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159021/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553" targetBox="[194,1140,142,1094]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1060,1125,1148]" box="[160,1060,1125,1148]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,252,1125,1148]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">Figure 3.</emphasis>
Paratype female of 
<taxonomicName box="[458,657,1125,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Aberropompilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dayi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[458,657,1125,1148]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">Aberropompilus dayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[666,747,1125,1148]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
:, lateral view. Scale bar: 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1156,1207,1508]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">
Mid coxa sharply raised and lamellate on dorso-outer surface. Fore tarsomere I shorter than tarsomeres 
<potCollectionCode box="[352,365,1241,1265]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">II</potCollectionCode>
<emphasis box="[365,378,1242,1265]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">–</emphasis>
<potCollectionCode box="[378,399,1241,1265]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">IV</potCollectionCode>
combined. Mid and hind femora with basal ring, and small spines posterodorsally. Hind femur compressed laterally, its inner face flattened. Hind tibia with many short but strong spines dorsally, without scale-like teeth; apical spines equal in thickness but unequal in length, weakly splayed out (
<figureCitation box="[780,873,1345,1369]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">
Figure 
<date box="[861,881,1345,1369]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">2I</date>
</figureCitation>
). Apicoventral spine on hind tarsomere V and apicodorsal spine on hind tarsomere IV somewhat broadened basally and narrowly triangular.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1156,1207,1508]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">
Metasoma slender, fusiform (
<figureCitation box="[535,630,1449,1473]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[160,225,888,911]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[163,1153,142,857]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Holotype female of Aberropompilus dayi sp. nov.: (A, B) whole body (A, dorsal view; B, lateral view); (C) meso- and metapleura and propodeum, lateral view; (D) pterostigma; (E) fore wing; (F) hind wing; (G) fore leg, lateral view; (H) apical metasomal segments, ventral view; (I) apex of hind tibia, outer view. Scale bars: A – C, E – H = 1 mm; D, I = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/159020/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">Figure 2</figureCitation>
A). Tergum 1 with lateral crease. Sternum 
<potCollectionCode box="[1142,1155,1449,1473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">II</potCollectionCode>
without transverse groove.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
